---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

// SEO metadata
const title = "Privacy Policy - NeuDayAI | How We Protect Your Data";
const description = "Learn how NeuDayAI collects, uses, and protects your personal information. Our privacy policy explains your rights and choices regarding your data.";
const keywords = ["Privacy Policy", "NeuDayAI Privacy", "Data Protection", "Personal Information", "Privacy Rights", "Cookie Policy", "Information Security"];
---

<Layout 
  title={title}
  description={description}
  keywords={keywords}
  pageType="article"
>
  <main class="pt-32">
    <section class="py-20" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/WebPage">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-3xl">
        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-8" itemprop="headline">Privacy Policy</h1>
        
        <div class="prose lg:prose-lg" itemprop="mainContentOfPage">
          <p>Effective Date: June 5, 2024</p>
          
          <p>This Privacy Policy describes how NeuDayAI Technologies Pvt. Ltd. ("NeuDayAI", "we", "us", or "our") collects, uses, and discloses your information when you use our website, services, mobile applications, or otherwise interact with us, including through Meta platforms (Facebook, WhatsApp, Instagram) and the WhatsApp Cloud API. We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring the security of your personal information.</p>
          
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">1. Information We Collect</h2>
          
          <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-6 mb-3">1.1 Information You Provide to Us</h3>
          <p>We may collect information you provide directly to us when you:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mt-2">
            <li>Fill out forms on our website</li>
            <li>Create an account or register for our services</li>
            <li>Subscribe to newsletters or communications</li>
            <li>Request customer support</li>
            <li>Participate in surveys, contests, or promotions</li>
            <li>Engage with us through contractual relationships</li>
            <li>Access our services through Meta (Facebook) Login or other social media platforms</li>
            <li>Use our applications distributed through Meta platforms, App Store, or Play Store</li>
            <li>Interact with us through WhatsApp Business messaging or chatbots</li>
            <li>Send messages to our WhatsApp Business accounts</li>
          </ul>
          <p>This information may include your name, email address, phone number, company name, job title, WhatsApp messages and media, and any other information you choose to provide.</p>
          
          <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-6 mb-3">1.2 Information from Meta and Third-Party Platforms</h3>
          <p>When you access our services through Meta platforms (Facebook, WhatsApp, Instagram) or other social media platforms, we may collect:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mt-2">
            <li><strong>Basic Profile Information:</strong> Name, email address, profile picture, and user ID</li>
            <li><strong>Public Profile Data:</strong> Information you have made publicly available on your Meta profile</li>
            <li><strong>Friends List:</strong> Information about your connections (only if explicitly granted permission)</li>
            <li><strong>Access Tokens:</strong> Authentication tokens that allow us to verify your identity</li>
            <li><strong>App-Specific Data:</strong> Information generated through your use of our Meta-integrated applications</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-6 mb-3">1.2.1 WhatsApp Cloud API Data</h3>
          <p>When you interact with our services through WhatsApp Business messaging, we may collect and process:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mt-2">
            <li><strong>Message Content:</strong> Text messages, voice messages, images, documents, and other media you send to our WhatsApp Business accounts</li>
            <li><strong>Phone Number:</strong> Your WhatsApp phone number for identification and communication purposes</li>
            <li><strong>Message Metadata:</strong> Timestamps, delivery status, read receipts, and message IDs</li>
            <li><strong>Profile Information:</strong> Your WhatsApp display name and profile picture (if made visible to businesses)</li>
            <li><strong>Conversation History:</strong> Previous interactions with our WhatsApp Business services</li>
            <li><strong>Status Information:</strong> Online status and last seen information (subject to your WhatsApp privacy settings)</li>
          </ul>
          
          <p>We only collect this information with your explicit consent and in accordance with Meta's Platform Policy, WhatsApp Business Policy, and applicable privacy laws.</p>
          
          <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-6 mb-3">1.3 Information We Collect Automatically</h3>
          <p>When you access or use our website or services, we may automatically collect certain information, including:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mt-2">
            <li>Usage Information: We collect information about your interactions with our website, including pages visited, features used, and actions taken.</li>
            <li>Device Information: We collect information about the device you use to access our services, including hardware model, operating system, unique device identifiers, and mobile network information.</li>
            <li>Log Information: We collect standard server logs, including IP addresses, browser type, referring/exit pages, operating system, date/time stamps, and clickstream data.</li>
            <li>Cookies and Similar Technologies: We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to collect information about your browsing activities. For more information, please see the "Cookies and Similar Technologies" section below.</li>
            <li>Meta Platform Analytics: Usage data from our applications on Meta platforms, including app interactions, session duration, and feature usage.</li>
            <li>WhatsApp API Analytics: Message delivery statistics, conversation metrics, and service performance data (anonymized and aggregated).</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
          <p>We use the information we collect for various purposes, including to:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mt-2">
            <li>Provide, maintain, and improve our services</li>
            <li>Process and fulfill your requests</li>
            <li>Communicate with you about products, services, offers, and events</li>
            <li>Respond to your comments, questions, and requests</li>
            <li>Monitor and analyze trends, usage, and activities</li>
            <li>Detect, investigate, and prevent security incidents and fraudulent transactions</li>
            <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
            <li>Personalize your experience</li>
            <li>Develop new products and services</li>
            <li>Authenticate your identity through Meta Login services</li>
            <li>Provide social features and integrations where applicable</li>
            <li>Analyze app performance and user engagement on Meta platforms</li>
            <li>Deliver customer support and automated responses through WhatsApp</li>
            <li>Send notifications, updates, and service-related messages via WhatsApp</li>
            <li>Analyze conversation patterns to improve our AI and chatbot responses</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-6 mb-3">2.1 Meta Platform-Specific Usage</h3>
          <p>For applications and services accessed through Meta platforms, we may use your information to:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mt-2">
            <li>Enable social login and account creation</li>
            <li>Provide personalized content and recommendations</li>
            <li>Facilitate social sharing features (with your permission)</li>
            <li>Improve app functionality based on Meta platform guidelines</li>
            <li>Comply with Meta's Platform Policy and Terms of Service</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-6 mb-3">2.2 WhatsApp Cloud API Usage</h3>
          <p>For interactions through WhatsApp Business messaging, we use your information to:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mt-2">
            <li>Respond to your inquiries and provide customer support</li>
            <li>Send automated responses and chatbot interactions</li>
            <li>Deliver service notifications, appointment reminders, and updates</li>
            <li>Process orders, bookings, or service requests</li>
            <li>Provide technical support and troubleshooting assistance</li>
            <li>Analyze message content to improve our AI-powered responses</li>
            <li>Maintain conversation history for context in ongoing communications</li>
            <li>Ensure message delivery and track conversation metrics for service improvement</li>
          </ul>
          
