            <p class="text-amber-800"><strong>WhatsApp Data Processing:</strong> We process WhatsApp messages and media only for the purposes of providing our services. We do not use WhatsApp data for advertising or marketing to third parties.</p>
          </div>
          
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">3. Disclosure of Information</h2>
          <p>We may share your information in the following circumstances:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mt-2">
            <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> We may share your information with third-party vendors, consultants, and other service providers who perform services on our behalf.</li>
            <li><strong>Meta Platform Integration:</strong> When you use our services through Meta platforms, certain information may be shared with Meta in accordance with their Data Policy and our agreements with them. This includes authentication data, app usage analytics, and technical information necessary for platform functionality.</li>
            <li><strong>Business Transfers:</strong> If we are involved in a merger, acquisition, or sale of all or a portion of our assets, your information may be transferred as part of that transaction.</li>
            <li><strong>Legal Requirements:</strong> We may disclose your information if required to do so by law or in response to valid requests by public authorities.</li>
            <li><strong>Protection of Rights:</strong> We may disclose information to protect the rights, property, or safety of NeuDayAI, our customers, or others.</li>
            <li><strong>With Your Consent:</strong> We may share your information with third parties when we have your consent to do so.</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-6 mb-3">3.1 Meta Data Sharing Limitations</h3>
          <div class="bg-blue-50 p-6 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-blue-500 mb-4">
            <p class="text-blue-800">We do not sell, trade, or rent your personal information obtained through Meta platforms to third parties for marketing purposes. Any data sharing with Meta is strictly limited to what is necessary for service functionality and platform compliance.</p>
          </div>
          
